Reasoning: The paper discusses the performance of spatially-coupled LDPC codes over a binary erasure channel, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the asymptotic properties of these codes, which is related to number theory (cs.NT). The use of scaling laws to predict performance is a topic related to statistical physics (cs.SI). The development of analytic tools for code design is related to distributed systems (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
